---

<ToolLayout
  title="Meta Tag Generator - SEO & Social Media Tags | Webutilbox"
  description="Generate complete HTML meta tags for SEO, Open Graph, and Twitter Cards. Preview how your page appears in search results. Free meta tag generator."
  canonical={canonical}
  ogImage="https://webutilbox.com/assets/og/og-generators.svg"
  keywords="meta tag generator, SEO tags, open graph, twitter cards, meta tags, HTML meta"
  h1="🏷️ Meta Tag Generator"
  subtitle="Generate SEO-optimized meta tags for your website and social media."
  lastUpdated=""
  shareText="Free%20online%20Meta%20Tag%20Generator%20on%20Webutilbox.%20Privacy-focused%2C%20runs%20100%25%20in%20your%20browser."
  shareUrl={canonical}
  embedUrl={canonical}
  embedTitle="Meta Tag Generator - SEO & Social Media Tags -- Webutilbox"
  embedHeight={600}
  toolCss={true}
  jsonLd={jsonLd}
>

<div class="workspace" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 15px;">
            <!-- Left: Input -->
            <div>
                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 12px;">
                    <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 600;">Basic SEO</div>
                    
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Page Title</label>
                        <input type="text" id="title" placeholder="Your Page Title - Brand Name" maxlength="60" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                        <div style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 4px;">
                            <span id="titleCount">0</span>/60 characters (optimal: 50-60)
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Description</label>
                        <textarea id="description" placeholder="Brief description of your page content..." maxlength="160" style="width: 100%; height: 70px; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem; resize: vertical;"></textarea>
                        <div style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 4px;">
                            <span id="descCount">0</span>/160 characters (optimal: 150-160)
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Keywords (comma-separated)</label>
                        <input type="text" id="keywords" placeholder="keyword1, keyword2, keyword3" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Author</label>
                        <input type="text" id="author" placeholder="Author name" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Canonical URL</label>
                        <input type="url" id="canonical" placeholder="https://example.com/page" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-bottom: 12px;">
                    <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 600;">Open Graph (Facebook, LinkedIn)</div>
                    
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">OG Title</label>
                        <input type="text" id="ogTitle" placeholder="Leave empty to use page title" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">OG Description</label>
                        <textarea id="ogDescription" placeholder="Leave empty to use page description" style="width: 100%; height: 60px; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem; resize: vertical;"></textarea>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">OG Image URL</label>
                        <input type="url" id="ogImage" placeholder="https://example.com/image.jpg" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                        <div style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 4px;">Recommended: 1200x630px</div>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">OG Type</label>
                        <select id="ogType" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                            <option value="website">Website</option>
                            <option value="article">Article</option>
                            <option value="product">Product</option>
                            <option value="video">Video</option>
                            <option value="music">Music</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">OG URL</label>
                        <input type="url" id="ogUrl" placeholder="Leave empty to use canonical URL" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                    <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 12px; font-weight: 600;">Twitter Card</div>
                    
                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Card Type</label>
                        <select id="twitterCard" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                            <option value="summary">Summary</option>
                            <option value="summary_large_image">Summary Large Image</option>
                            <option value="app">App</option>
                            <option value="player">Player</option>
                        </select>
                    </div>

                    <div style="margin-bottom: 12px;">
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Twitter Site Handle</label>
                        <input type="text" id="twitterSite" placeholder="@yourusername" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>

                    <div>
                        <label style="font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 6px; display: block; color: var(--gray);">Twitter Creator Handle</label>
                        <input type="text" id="twitterCreator" placeholder="@creatorusername" style="width: 100%; padding: 10px; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 6px; color: var(--white); font-size: 0.85rem;">
                    </div>
                </div>

                <button id="generateBtn" style="width: 100%; margin-top: 12px; padding: 12px; background: var(--primary); border: none; border-radius: 6px; color: white; cursor: pointer; font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 500;">Generate Meta Tags</button>
            </div>

            <!-- Right: Output -->
            <div>
                <div style="display: flex; justify-content: space-between; align-items: center; margin-bottom: 8px;">
                    <label style="font-size: 0.8rem; color: var(--gray);">Generated Meta Tags</label>
                    <button id="copyBtn" style="padding: 6px 12px; font-size: 0.75rem; background: var(--primary); border: none; border-radius: 4px; color: white; cursor: pointer;">📋 Copy All</button>
                </div>
                <textarea id="output" readonly placeholder="Generated meta tags will appear here..." style="width: 100%; height: 520px; padding: 12px; font-size: 0.8rem; background: var(--dark); border: 1px solid var(--border); border-radius: 8px; color: var(--white); font-family: 'Courier New', monospace; resize: vertical; line-height: 1.6;"></textarea>

                <!-- Preview -->
                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 12px;">
                    <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: 600;">Search Preview</div>
                    <div id="searchPreview" style="background: var(--dark); padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                        <div style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: #10b981; margin-bottom: 4px;">https://example.com</div>
                        <div style="font-size: 1rem; color: #8ab4f8; margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 500;" id="previewTitle">Your Page Title</div>
                        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: #bdc1c6; line-height: 1.4;" id="previewDesc">Your page description will appear here...</div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div style="background: var(--light); border-radius: 8px; padding: 15px; border: 1px solid var(--border); margin-top: 12px;">
                    <div style="font-size: 0.85rem; color: var(--gray); margin-bottom: 10px; font-weight: 600;">Social Preview</div>
                    <div id="socialPreview" style="background: var(--dark); padding: 12px; border-radius: 6px; border: 1px solid var(--border);">
                        <div style="background: #1a1a1a; height: 150px; border-radius: 6px; margin-bottom: 8px; display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; color: var(--gray); font-size: 0.75rem;" id="previewImage">
                            1200 x 630
                        </div>
                        <div style="font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--white); margin-bottom: 4px; font-weight: 600;" id="previewOgTitle">Your Page Title</div>
                        <div style="font-size: 0.75rem; color: var(--gray); line-height: 1.4;" id="previewOgDesc">Your page description...</div>
                        <div style="font-size: 0.7rem; color: var(--gray); margin-top: 6px; text-transform: uppercase;">EXAMPLE.COM</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        
        <!-- Share Bar -->




<script src="/js/meta-tag-generator.js" defer></script>

<div class="info-section" slot="info">
<h2>Meta Tag Generator - SEO and Social Media Tags Made Easy</h2>
            <p>Our free Meta Tag Generator creates all the HTML meta tags your website needs for better search engine rankings and rich social media previews. Fill in your page details and get a complete, copy-ready block of meta tags covering basic SEO, Open Graph, and Twitter Cards — all in one click.</p>

            <h3>What Are Meta Tags and Why Do They Matter?</h3>
            <p>Meta tags are snippets of HTML code placed in the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> section of a web page. They don't appear visibly on the page itself, but they communicate critical information to search engines and social media platforms about what your page contains.</p>
            <p>The title and description meta tags directly influence how your page appears in Google search results. A well-crafted title (50–60 characters) and description (150–160 characters) can significantly improve your click-through rate, even if your ranking stays the same. Open Graph tags control how your page looks when shared on Facebook, LinkedIn, and other platforms — including the image, title, and description shown in the link preview card.</p>
            <p>Twitter Cards work similarly but are specific to Twitter/X. Without these tags, social platforms will either show a generic preview or pull random content from your page, which often looks unprofessional and reduces engagement.</p>

            <h3>Generated Meta Tag Types</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Basic SEO tags: title, description, keywords, author, and canonical URL</li>
                <li>Open Graph tags for Facebook, LinkedIn, and other OG-compatible platforms</li>
                <li>Twitter Card tags with support for summary and summary_large_image formats</li>
                <li>Live character counters for title (60 max) and description (160 max)</li>
                <li>Real-time Google search result preview</li>
                <li>Social media link preview card simulation</li>
                <li>One-click copy of all generated tags to clipboard</li>
                <li>Support for OG types: website, article, product, video, and music</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>How to Use the Meta Tag Generator</h3>
            <p>Generating your meta tags takes just a few minutes. Follow these steps:</p>
            <ul>
                <li>Step 1: Enter your page title — keep it under 60 characters for best results in search.</li>
                <li>Step 2: Write a compelling description between 150–160 characters that summarizes the page.</li>
                <li>Step 3: Add relevant keywords, your author name, and the canonical URL of the page.</li>
                <li>Step 4: Fill in the Open Graph section — you can reuse the title and description or write social-specific versions.</li>
                <li>Step 5: Set your Twitter Card type and handles, then click "Generate Meta Tags".</li>
                <li>Step 6: Click "Copy All" and paste the tags into the <code>&lt;head&gt;</code> of your HTML file.</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Improving SEO with Meta Tags</h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Optimizing blog posts and articles for search engine visibility</li>
                <li>Setting up Open Graph tags for e-commerce product pages</li>
                <li>Improving social media sharing previews for landing pages</li>
                <li>Adding Twitter Cards to news articles and media content</li>
                <li>Generating canonical tags to prevent duplicate content issues</li>
                <li>Creating consistent meta tags across a multi-page website</li>
            </ul>

            <h3>Writing Effective Meta Descriptions</h3>
            <p>Your page title is the single most important meta tag for SEO. Include your primary keyword near the beginning of the title, and keep it under 60 characters to avoid truncation in search results. Avoid keyword stuffing — write for humans first, search engines second.</p>
            <p>For Open Graph images, use a 1200×630 pixel image for the best display across all platforms. This is the recommended size for Facebook, LinkedIn, and Twitter large card previews. Make sure the image URL is absolute (starting with https://) and publicly accessible — social crawlers can't access images behind authentication.</p>
            <p>Don't skip the canonical URL tag. If your content is accessible at multiple URLs (with and without trailing slashes, with query parameters, etc.), the canonical tag tells search engines which version is the "official" one, preventing duplicate content penalties.</p>

            

            <h3>Tags Generated Client-Side Only</h3>
            <p>Tag generation runs in your browser. No page data is sent to any server.</p>
        
            <h3>Frequently Asked Questions</h3>
            <div class="faq-list">
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What meta tags are most important for SEO?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>The most important meta tags are: title (shown in search results, 50-60 chars), meta description (shown in search snippets, 150-160 chars), canonical URL (prevents duplicate content), and Open Graph tags (og:title, og:description, og:image) for social sharing. The keywords meta tag is no longer used by Google.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is the Open Graph protocol?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Open Graph (OG) is a protocol created by Facebook that controls how your page appears when shared on social media. og:title, og:description, og:image, and og:url are the four essential tags. Twitter has its own similar system called Twitter Cards.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What size should my og:image be?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>The recommended og:image size is 1200x630 pixels (1.91:1 aspect ratio). This displays well on Facebook, LinkedIn, and most platforms. Twitter recommends 1200x600 for summary_large_image cards. Use a PNG or JPG under 8MB.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">What is a canonical URL and why does it matter?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>A canonical URL tells search engines which version of a page is the 'official' one when the same content is accessible at multiple URLs (e.g., with and without www, with different query parameters). Without it, search engines may split ranking signals across duplicate pages.</p></div>
                </div>
                <div class="faq-item">
                    <button class="faq-question" onclick="toggleFaq(this)">How do I test my meta tags?</button>
                    <div class="faq-answer"><p>Use the Facebook Sharing Debugger (developers.facebook.com/tools/debug), Twitter Card Validator (cards-dev.twitter.com/validator), and LinkedIn Post Inspector to preview how your page looks when shared. Google Search Console shows how your title and description appear in search results.</p></div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="related-tools">
                <h3>Related Tools</h3>
                <div class="related-tools-grid">
                    <a href="../slug-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Slug Generator</a>
                    <a href="../markdown-to-html/" class="related-tool-link">Markdown to HTML</a>
                    <a href="../html-entity-encoder/" class="related-tool-link">HTML Entity Encoder</a>
                    <a href="../url-parser/" class="related-tool-link">URL Parser</a>
                    <a href="../favicon-generator/" class="related-tool-link">Favicon Generator</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
</div>

</ToolLayout>